---
description: Create a PR, enable auto-merge, and open it in the browser
---

Create a pull request using the GitHub CLI, enable auto-merge, and then open it in your web browser.

Steps:
1. Check the current git status and branch
2. Review the changes that will be included in the PR
3. Create a PR using `gh pr create` with a concise body (max 5 sentences, ideally 2). Do not add section titles or formatting - just a brief description of the current change.
4. Enable auto-merge with `gh pr merge --auto`
5. Open the PR in your browser using `gh pr view --web`
